##That's hard to believe, but I don't think he's GonNa be able to make it

Micro Signal Xiezuozheyunshegong

FUNCTION INTRODUCTION: Volunteer Information Management, social worker information management, public welfare information release, social work professional exchange

This article is one of the case interviews conducted by the collaborators in the "Peasant Workers' anti-epidemic Rescue Action" , aiming at quickly identifying the vulnerable groups and their needs in the epidemic situation, and providing reference for the epidemic prevention, control and rescue work, we put it together and share it with you.

Deep breathing in case of an outbreak
A case study on the plight of migrant workers in Foshan (10)

If we don't work, we work. We don't have any money

Narrator: Liu Xing
Place of employment: Beijing
Editor's Note: Liu Xing, 51, who moved to Beijing from rural Inner Mongolia in 1988, is blind in his right eye and has cataracts in his left eye. Now I'm a car attendant. 36-year-old wife, second-degree intellectual disability, unemployed. His son, a 16 year old Ninth grade student, is quiet and unsure about his future.

I graduated from junior high school, my education is not high. In 1988, I came to Beijing to work with a cousin who was a soldier in Beijing. Having no place to stay when I first arrived, I stopped in Beijing and was picked up by the police and sent to a shelter several times. Over the years, I have been engaged in a variety of work, in recent years vision is getting worse and worse, a lot of work can not do.
A good horse is ridden and a good man is bullied

After the great fire in 2017, we moved to Muxiyuan, which was not a good place to live. This side people bully, I usually work at home, the neighbors think my family no one, honest, anyway, is a horse good people ride, people good people bully. There are two times almost conflict, and then explain to them, we are all to Beijing to work, acquaintance is fate. They said, "who's your destiny? "

I also told the landlord that they bullied us, that the laundry we did in the yard couldn't be found hanging out the door, and that once my bike was left outside to get shit on, toilet paper, etc. . There are four families in this hospital. They're all relatives. The landlord said, "we have changed houses several times now, just because we are not in harmony with these families. They have lived in this courtyard for more than 10 years and don't want anyone else to live here. " Later, they accepted that we were being bullied, he doesn't say anything, but it's okay.

Co-author social worker visits Liu Xing's home (summer 2019)
In a month, there's barely any money left

I'm a car attendant now. It's $3,000 a month. I can't see very well. I can't see straight. In the summer of 2019, the leadership let me rest for more than a month, that is, do not want me, also did not pay me. Then I called the maitre d', said the family is not easy, just let me on. 5,000,6,000 yuan for tuition, you have to borrow money from friends and relatives, you have to put in a good word with the school, and you have to pay it later. Every time is to wait for me to work for two or three months to pay off the tuition money borrowed, but soon had to pay next semester's tuition, always so come over.

At present, our rent, water and electricity is 1,000 yuan a month, the children's school is 40 miles away from home, the bus to school is more than 100 yuan a month, breakfast is 200 yuan a month, a month down almost no money. This New Year for the children to buy a pair of cotton-padded shoes, we did not buy any clothes, can make do with it.

The mother, who has a second degree mental disability, started paying 300 yuan a month the year before last. I heard someone in her hometown had received nine hundred yuan, and we couldn't confirm that in Beijing. She's always complaining about headaches, having to buy medicine every month, and the doctor says she's got a nervous headache, and that mental retardation affects the brain. She's supposed to take pills all the time, but they're too expensive, and given our financial situation, if we have the money, we buy them. If we don't, we don't. We have the new rural cooperative medical scheme, but we can only offer 50% . We have done it once before, and we can only offer it six months later. Because you are not at home, he does not want to report, you have to constantly urge him, always delayed, and we can not buy drugs in Beijing reimbursement. I asked the head of the village and the branch secretary, they think that as long as you have the ability to go out to work, the village thinks you have the ability to live, do not give you calculate subsistence. The cost of the medicine is not calculated, is the hands of every month have no money.

I am blind in this eye, and one is also highly myopic. In September 2019, I suddenly saw something that felt like fog. Go to the hospital to check that is cataract, experts say surgery is too risky, because only one eye has vision, done this, if not see over. There was no surgery in the back, and I couldn't even see the bike in front of me when I went to work. In 2017, after moving to work farther, every bus interval of one hour, in order to chase the bus, I ran with others, the eye is not good, hit the roadside pipe, tooth activity, a year to recover.
I don't go out. I have two old thermal masks

On the first day of the Lunar New Year, the leadership said that let me rest not to go to work, when also do not know. The community has been posted on the wall since January 29th, let to wear a mask, not allowed to go around, there are also security guard in the alley, ask you where you are from, have ID card? There's not a lot of people around. There's a lot of garbage in front of our alley, blocked by Lattes, and I don't see anyone spraying disinfectant.

The entrance to Liu Xing's rental house (summer 2019)

I read on the news that it's transmitted by breathing, spitting, whatever. Few people come out these days. They wear masks. People don't wander around anymore. We don't know of any quarantines around here. I just read the news on my phone and know the precautions. I wear a mask, wash my hands frequently, and try not to touch people, and don't go anywhere where there are people.

I have two of my own thermal masks that I bought to keep me warm, and I have very little contact with people. When I get to work, I'll think about buying one of those special masks. I'll tell the kid to stay home with his mom and try not to leave the house.

Now the disease is quite severe, working hours are always extended, one will say is the seventh day, now say is the tenth day, and said the development of the epidemic again. Our individual unit is not like the state-owned, do not work no money. This is not a matter of urgency, we must put the state of mind, do not be nervous, pay attention to the body.
If we don't work, we have to work. We don't have any money

It's hard to say how long this outbreak will last, but we'll have to watch it day by day. If we don't go to work, WE'RE GONNA have to eat, but we don't have any money to eat. The outbreak of a sudden, at first ignored, now began to grasp, I am worried about not working no salary, no money to pay school fees.

I also thought if I wasn't allowed to go back to work here, I'd find another job. But now can not look for, because he has not said do not want me, our work of this car manager, said the point is not crooked melon cracked jujube is ill, good people do not do this job. Now this epidemic even if many people ask for jobs, also can not go to work, can only first understand the information. I can't see. I want to do a lot of work, and they don't want me.
The teacher won't let him into the classroom without paying his tuition

The children's school's Wechat group from January 23 until now, let every student daily report a safe. But when to go to school always have to wait for notice, online class what the teacher has not mentioned.

Angels at home with Liu Xing's children (September 2019)

If I can't go to work all the time, I'll worry about my kids'tuition. On one previous occasion when the tuition fee was one thousand yuan, the teacher would not let the child into the classroom, not into the classroom for four days, and then borrowed money from others to pay to let them in. I want to wait for my child to go to Dalian Vocational High School after graduating from junior high school this year, where there are relatives to take care of him. If I can't make it in Beijing, I'll go home with his mother.

Angels at home with Liu Xing's children (September 2019)

I always tell my kids, if you want to stay in the city, you have to study hard to get a good job. Working is not the same as getting a real job. If the formal work, a day to work eight hours, working hours, pay is also high, protected by law, all good. If you are a temporary worker, you can quit if you say so. You may not have a pension until you are 80 or 100. I used to think that when he came to work, I would take her mother to find another job, save some money for the children to have a family, but now look at me this body is not good, also can not earn a few money, the future can only rely on their own.

Social Worker's notes


After talking to Liu Xing on the phone, he could always feel his yearning for a stable life, especially for his children's future, hoping that they would study hard and find a regular job and settle down in the city. But how hard it is for a family where both husband and wife are disabled. Liu Xing's eyesight was failing, but in his own way he struggled to maintain the dignity of work and, through hard work and patience, to be a good worker, husband and father. But the epidemic makes his work and life uncertain, a stable life and a better future for his children, seems to have become a luxury. And can the social security system give more security and dignity to these workers who work in other places?

Service advice
Now:

1. Coordination of relief resources and provision of emergency life support;
2. To provide personalized epidemic prevention knowledge guidance for family members, link the necessary protective supplies;
3. To assist families to understand the progress of work units, epidemic prevention information near the community, and follow up the children's studies, so as to prepare for the restoration of normal life order;
4. To understand children's learning, social and psychological needs through online communication during the epidemic, and to encourage them to participate in the online communication and counseling of collaborators.

LONG-TERM:
1. Combining the physical condition of their family members, provide them with employment capacity-building services to enhance the level of family employment;
2. Link to accompany Angel Volunteers to provide homework counseling, career planning and support for children;
3. Continue to provide financial aid to children;
4. Link Medical Volunteers and medical assistance resources to provide health and medical consultation and medical assistance to family members.

4. To understand children's learning, social and psychological needs through online communication during the epidemic, and to encourage them to participate in the online communication and counseling of collaborators.

LONG-TERM:

1. Combining the physical condition of their family members, provide them with employment capacity-building services to enhance the level of family employment;

2. Link to accompany Angel Volunteers to provide homework counseling, career planning and support for children;
3. Continue to provide financial aid to children;
4. Link Medical Volunteers and medical assistance resources to provide health and medical consultation and medical assistance to family members.

(more case stories and case reports can be found on the wechat public account "collaborator Cloud Social Worker" . Please leave a message behind the public account to contact the collaborator.)

Thank you to each and every one of our collaborators. In these extraordinary times, there is always hope and strength in our hearts, even if we have to keep our distance from each other. THANKS FOR HAVING YOU!
